ghetto /ˈɡɛtəʊ/

(ghettoes) 

1. N-COUNT A ghetto is a part of a city in which many poor people or many people of a particular race, religion, or nationality live separately from everyone else. 贫民区; (相同种族、宗教或国籍的人的) 聚居区 

例： ...the black ghettos of New York and Los Angeles. …纽约和洛杉矶的黑人聚居区。

